Janab-e-Alaa, the origin of Lucknow is a bit of a mystery, but there are a few theories. One theory is that it was founded by the Nawab Asaf-ud-Daula in 1775. Another theory is that it was founded by the British in 1856. However, archaeological findings suggest that Lucknow is a much older city, dating back to at least the 13th century.

Whatever its origins, Lucknow has a rich and fascinating history. It was once the capital of the Awadh region, and it was a major center of culture and learning. Today, Lucknow is a vibrant and cosmopolitan city, and it is home to a number of historical and cultural landmarks."}

